                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_dyǵyzæ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dyǵyzæ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>digiza</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мамка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mother</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кормилица</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>nurse</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>воспитательница</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>governess</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>omæn æ digiza — Madæ xwarz Majræn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ее мамка — славная богоматерь (Мать Мария)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>her mother is the glorious mother of God (Mother Mary)</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 136</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>adtæj ungæ mæ digiza</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>улица была моей воспитательницей</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the street was my teacher</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>omæn æ digiza — Madæ xwarz Majræn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ее мамка — славная богоматерь (Мать Мария)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>her mother is the glorious mother of God (Mother Mary)</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 136</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>adtæj ungæ mæ digiza</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>улица была моей воспитательницей</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the street was my teacher</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Сближается с <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>dəgəzä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>dəgəza</w> <gloss><q>нянька</q></gloss></mentioned>. Возможно, тюркское слово, образованное из <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>degi(š)</w> <gloss><q>замена</q></gloss></mentioned> + <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ize</w> <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>III 1659</biblScope></bibl>), буквально „заменяющая мать“.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It relates to <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>dəgəzä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>dəgəza</w> <gloss><q>nurse</q></gloss></mentioned>. Possibly a Turkic word derived from <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>degi(š)</w> <gloss><q>substitute</q></gloss></mentioned> + <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ize</w> <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned> (Cf. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>III 1659</biblScope></bibl>), literally “replacing mother”.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>